        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 12:00AM MDT by NWS Rapid City SD</headline>
        <description>At 1200 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 5 miles southeast of Chance, or 25 miles north of
Faith, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Meadow, Chance, Usta, Glad Valley, Thunder Butte, Iron Lightning,
Owen Lake, and Arrow Head Buttes.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
